            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "First of all, don't report issues just by linking to other issues. Describe the actually relevant problem, concisely. In this case it is:\n\n> when quit neovim. the lsp doesn't close and keep running with cpu 100%\n\n\nAlso, https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/36752#issuecomment-3596017419 may be relevant.\n\n> See also [#19672](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/19672). Not blocking on exit with the `false` default was intentional\n\nNote:\n\n- Nvim calls \"shutdown\" to all LSes when Nvim is exiting.\n- If you want Nvim to force-stop the LS if it doesn't stop itself, set `ClientConfig.exit_timeout`\n    - Requires latest Nvim 0.12 (not 0.11)",
